    41	
    42	---
    43	
    44	## What Consumers Should Expect
    45	
    46	Products import focused SDK packages from this repo. The v1 baseline (stable for product adapter work):
    47	
    48	- `@relay-assistant/core`
    49	- `@relay-assistant/sessions`
    50	- `@relay-assistant/surfaces`
    51	
    52	Beyond v1 (implemented, review before consuming):
    53	
    54	- `@relay-assistant/coordination`
    55	- `@relay-assistant/connectivity`
    56	- `@relay-assistant/routing` (**gated** — routing tests below DoD; see above)
    57	
    58	Planned for future milestones:
    59	
    60	- `@relay-assistant/memory` — v1.1
    61	- `@relay-assistant/traits` — v1.2
    62	- `@relay-assistant/proactive` — v1.2
    63	- `@relay-assistant/policy` — v2
    64	
    65	Products such as Sage, MSD, and NightCTO should use this repo for reusable assistant runtime behavior while keeping their own domain logic, prompts, tools, UI, and product policy in their own repositories.
    66	
    67	---
    68	
    69	## Layer Model
    70	
    71	### Relay foundation stays elsewhere
    72	
    73	Keep these concerns in Relay family repos such as `relay`, `gateway`, `relaycron`, `relayauth`, and `relayfile`:
    74	
    75	- transport adapters and webhook verification
    76	- normalized inbound/outbound message primitives
    77	- channel/session transport substrate
    78	- auth and connection wiring
    79	- low-level action dispatch
    80	- scheduler and wake-up infrastructure
    81	- relaycast and transport observability
    82	
    83	### Assistant SDK lives here
    84	
    85	This repo should own reusable assistant behavior built on top of Relay primitives:
    86	
    87	- assistant construction and lifecycle
    88	- memory scopes and adapters
    89	- proactive engines and watch rules
    90	- assistant session models
    91	- assistant-facing surface contracts
    92	- specialist coordination
    93	- action policy and audit integration
    94	
    95	### Product logic stays in product repos
    96	
    97	Keep these concerns in Sage, MSD, NightCTO, and future product repositories:
    98	
    99	- prompts, workforce persona definitions, and persona behavior beyond baseline identity
   100	- product-specific workflows and tools
   101	- domain-specific watchers and automations
   102	- product UX and dashboards
   103	- pricing, tiering, escalation, and customer policy
   104	
   105	> **Workforce persona vs. assistant traits:** Workforce personas are runtime execution profiles (model, harness, system prompt, tier). Assistant traits are identity and behavioral characteristics (voice, style, vocabulary, proactivity). These are distinct. See [traits and persona layer](docs/architecture/traits-and-persona-layer.md) for the full boundary definition.
   106	
   107	---
   108	
   109	## Package Map
   110	
   111	| Package | Purpose | Status |
   112	| --- | --- | --- |
   113	| `@relay-assistant/core` | Assistant definition, lifecycle, shared runtime composition | **IMPLEMENTED** |
   114	| `@relay-assistant/sessions` | Cross-surface session identity, resume, attachment rules | **IMPLEMENTED** |
   115	| `@relay-assistant/surfaces` | Assistant-facing surface abstractions above Relay transport | **IMPLEMENTED** |
   116	| `@relay-assistant/routing` | Model-choice, latency/depth/cost routing, workload-router-aligned policy | **IMPLEMENTED** (DoD gap — see above) |
   117	| `@relay-assistant/connectivity` | Efficient inter-agent signaling, convergence, escalation, and communication contracts | **IMPLEMENTED** |
   118	| `@relay-assistant/coordination` | Coordinator/specialist orchestration and synthesis contracts | **IMPLEMENTED** |
   119	| `@relay-assistant/traits` | Assistant identity traits: voice, style, vocabulary, behavioral defaults, surface formatting preferences | **planned — v1.2** |
   120	| `@relay-assistant/memory` | Memory scopes, stores, retrieval, promotion, compaction hooks | placeholder — v1.1 |
   121	| `@relay-assistant/proactive` | Follow-up engines, watch rules, scheduler bindings | placeholder — v1.2 |
   122	| `@relay-assistant/policy` | Approvals, external-action safeguards, audit hooks | placeholder — v2 |
   123	| `@relay-assistant/examples` | Reference adoption examples, not production product code | placeholder |
   124	
   125	---
