   138	- [Connectivity adoption guide](docs/consumer/connectivity-adoption-guide.md)
   139	- [Connectivity patterns research](docs/research/connectivity-patterns.md)
   140	- [Internal system comparison](docs/research/internal-system-comparison.md)
   141	- [Glossary](docs/reference/glossary.md)
   142	
   143	---
   144	
   145	## Implementation Direction
   146	
   147	This repository should become the OSS core.
   148	
   149	A later cloud implementation should be built on top of the OSS SDK in a separate package or repo, similar in spirit to other AgentWorkforce properties that keep the reusable core open-source and place Cloudflare-backed adapters and hosted infrastructure in a distinct cloud layer.
   150	
   151	That later cloud layer should depend on this SDK, not replace it.
   152	
   153	---
   154	
   155	## Initial Adoption Rule
   156	
   157	If a capability is reusable across multiple assistants with only configuration or adapter changes, it belongs here.
   158	
   159	If a capability depends on product-specific ontology, customer workflow, or product policy, it stays in the product repo.
   160	
   161	**Reuse-first rule for new package work:** Before authoring a new package implementation, inspect `relay` and related AgentWorkforce repos for reusable packages, contracts, or runtime capabilities. For memory specifically, treat `@relay-assistant/memory` as an assistant-facing adapter/composition layer over `@agent-relay/memory`, not a greenfield memory engine.
