    77	## WF-1: Define assistant and start runtime — **COMPLETE**
    78	
    79	**Package:** `core`
    80	**Status:** COMPLETE — 31 tests passing, `SPEC_RECONCILED`
    81	**Depends on:** `docs/specs/v1-core-spec.md` (`SPEC_RECONCILED` — Contradiction 1–3 resolutions applied)
    82	**Produces:** `AssistantDefinition`, `AssistantRuntime`, `createAssistant`, lifecycle state machine, `runtime.status()`
    83	**PR scope:** `packages/core/src/types.ts`, `packages/core/src/core.ts`, `packages/core/src/core.test.ts`
    84	
    85	### Steps
    86	
    87	1. Define an `AssistantDefinition` with `id`, `name`, and a `capabilities` map (`Record<string, CapabilityHandler>`)
    88	2. Call `createAssistant(definition, { inbound: stubAdapter, outbound: stubAdapter })` — returns `AssistantRuntime`
    89	3. Call `runtime.start()` — verify `runtime.status().ready === true`
    90	4. Call `runtime.stop()` — verify runtime is no longer accepting dispatches
    91	5. Verify double-start is idempotent or throws expected error
    92	6. Verify double-stop is idempotent or throws expected error
    93	
    94	### Acceptance criteria
    95	
    96	- `AssistantDefinition` interface is defined and exported from `packages/core/src/index.ts`
    97	- `AssistantRuntime` interface is defined and exported
    98	- `createAssistant` factory is exported; it validates `definition` and throws `AssistantDefinitionError` on invalid input
    99	- `runtime.status()` returns `RuntimeStatus` reflecting `ready`, `startedAt`, `registeredCapabilities`, `registeredSubsystems`, `inFlightHandlers`
   100	- At least one test exercises the full start/stop cycle with a stub relay adapter
   101	- No network calls, no side effects outside in-memory state
   102	- `RelayInboundAdapter` and `RelayOutboundAdapter` interfaces are exported (with `RelayInboundAdapter.onMessage` accepting `InboundMessage` per Contradiction 1 resolution)
